# Release & publish

When the user asks to prep, publish, push, or release Cozy Corkboard:

1. Read **AGENTS.md** and follow the release workflow in order.
2. Run `npm run release` to build and zip (uses electron-packager, not electron-builder).
3. User install instructions live in **README.md** — update version references when bumping.
4. Only commit or push when the user explicitly asks.
5. Create GitHub releases with `gh release create` and attach `release/cozy-corkboard-v{version}-win-x64.zip`.

Do not use electron-builder on Windows. Do not commit `dist/`, `release/`, or `node_modules/`.
